        <div class="row d-flex justify-content-center">
        <p class="parrafo col-8 col-xl-8 col-lg-8 col-md-6 col-sm-8">For the layout HTML and CSS were used. Data was extracted thorugh national and regional databases, that was later cleaned on Google Sheets. Only the information related to rain per river basin (first bar graph) was extracted with the program Tabula. It extracts data from pdf files. All graphs were created with Adobe Illsutrator and the images were obtained thorugh Google Satellite and the Copernicus website. The scrollytelling effect over the Laguna de Santa Olalla pictures was created with the JS library Scrollama.</p>
        </div>
